================================================================================
                               General Instructions
================================================================================
	
	To build the project properly you will need Apache Maven greater v2.2.0. 
	Please see <http://maven.apache.org/> for details and downloads.


================================================================================
                             Running The Project
================================================================================

1. 	Run the tomcat startup scripts:

		${project.dir}/apache-tomcat-6.0.20/bin/startup.bat 	on windows
		${project.dir}/apache-tomcat-6.0.20/bin/startup.sh 		on *unix

7.	Now you should invoke:

		mvn clean war:war tomcat:deploy
		
8. 	Open <http://localhost:8080/sloth> in your favorite web browser

================================================================================
                    Generate The Project Specific Documentation
================================================================================
1.	Open a Terminal and change to the project directory.
		
		
2.1		For source jar's:

			mvn source:jar source:test-jar 
		
2.2		For javadoc documentation:

			mvn javadoc:javadoc javadoc:test-javadoc
			
2.3		For packaged javadoc files:

			mvn javadoc:jar javadoc:test-jar
			
2.4		To package the complete project:

			mvn assembly:assembly
			
		This will exports the complete project to a tar.gz, tar.bz2 and a zip.

		
================================================================================
                         Opening Project in Eclipse IDE
================================================================================

1.	Open a Terminal and change to the project directory.
		
2.	Run:
		
		mvn eclipse:eclipse
	
	This will generate the required project files for Eclipse.

4.	Open Eclipse.

5.	Choose: 
		
		File -> Import -> General -> Existing Project into Workspace
		
	Select the project directory and hit Finish.

================================================================================
                         Opening Project in Netbeans IDE
================================================================================

	Simply open the project folder as an existing project.
